{"name":"Move Silently","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To move with preternatural quiet, even across squeaky floorboards, dry leaves, loose debris, and the like. This skill is executed at half the scout&rsquo;s normal movement rate.</p>\n<p>Scouts also practice almost all thievish skills. The following abilities improve as the scout advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"scout","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":5,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253287286,"modifiedTime":1681579325696,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"8BP8VPhDW0UfXp3t","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Run","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 112\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To move as swiftly as a hare; base 50 MV when lightly armoured or unarmoured.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"scout","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Q7eHkvfQRl80TQBF"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252890133,"modifiedTime":1681579325696,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"9dGvTaDjpWpXjsM4","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Open Locks","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To pick locks or disable latching mechanisms both magical and mundane. Thieves&rsquo; tools are required. Picking or dismantling a lock may be attempted but once; if the attempt fails, the scout cannot try again until he has gained a level of experience. Most locks require 1d4 minutes to pick; complex locks might necessitate 3d6 minutes.</p>\n<p>Scouts also practice almost all thievish skills. The following abilities improve as the scout advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"scout","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253307994,"modifiedTime":1681579325696,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"CVYIcNTx2Do9sC90","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Discern Noise","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To hearken at a door and detect the faintest of noises on the other side, perceive the distant footfalls of a wandering monster, or distinguish a single voice in a crowd. Six rounds (one minute) of concentrated listening are required.</p>\n<p>Scouts also practice almost all thievish skills. The following abilities improve as the scout advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"scout","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":4,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253207156,"modifiedTime":1681579325696,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"CfnVE0ThlZaVJwtV","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Manipulate Traps","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To find, remove, and reset traps both magical and mundane. Separate checks must be made to accomplish each facet of this skill: <em>find</em>, <em>remove</em>, <em>reset</em>. Failure by more than two, or if a natural 12 is rolled, may cause the trap to detonate on the scout. Also, a new trap may be built if the mechanism is simple and the parts available; anything more complex requires the assistance of an engineer. Thieves&rsquo; tools are required when practicing this ability.</p>\n<p>Scouts also practice almost all thievish skills. The following abilities improve as the scout advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"scout","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253249264,"modifiedTime":1681579325696,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"E4SJglsdZKD7zOjA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Extraordinary Dexterity","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 27\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+8% chance to perform <em>extraordinary feats of dexterity</em> (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>dexterity</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"acout","roll":"d100","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.MU9Ad6GulTFsmkIb"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679249969686,"modifiedTime":1681579325696,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"F2rSnU9nLMkg0lY4","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Determine Depth and Grade","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 112\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To ascertain the extent of a pit, chasm, or shaft by dropping a coin or pebble and listening; to determine the slope of dungeon passages, detecting even the shallowest of slants. The chance of success for determine depth and grade is as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1st to 4th level = 2-in-6</li>\n<li>5th to 8th level = 3-in-6</li>\n<li>9th to 12th level = 4-in-6</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the roll is off by one or two, the estimate is off by 20%. For example, if a 2nd-level scout rolls a 4 when attempting to determine the depth of a 50-foot pit, he or she will believe the pit to be either 60 feet deep or 40 feet deep, as best decided by the referee. If the roll is off by more than 2, then the result is failure.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"scout","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Q7eHkvfQRl80TQBF"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252890133,"modifiedTime":1681579325696,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"GAF8ViqRLsEk5Xa4","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Climb","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To ascend or descend sheer cliffs or walls without need of climbing gear. If vertical, the surface must be rough or cracked. At least one check must be made per 100 feet of climbing. Failure indicates the climber has slipped and fallen at about the midpoint of the check.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 113\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Scouts also practice almost all thievish skills. The following abilities improve as the scout advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"scout","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579325695,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"IjGinUaFzI1Ga4Kk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Controlled Fall","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 112\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To retard descent of precipitous drops. For every level of experience, the scout can fall 10 feet and sustain no damage, so long as a wall or other stable surface is within a five-foot reach throughout the descent. For falls beyond the scout&rsquo;s limit, normal rules are in force starting at the point at which the controlled fall no longer applies; e.g., a 5th-level scout plummets down a 90-foot pit and thus sustains 4d6 hp damage.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"scout","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252890133,"modifiedTime":1681579325695,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"Q7eHkvfQRl80TQBF","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Disguise","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 112\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To fashion a facÌ§ade that simulates a particular race/culture/social class, possibly making one appear a few inches taller or shorter and/or several pounds heavier or thinner (cf. the <em>disguise self</em> spell). The scout also can appear as the opposite sex. This ruse may be accomplished through a combination of acting, makeup, apparel, and perhaps even subtle sorcery. The base chance of the <em>disguise</em> being discerned is 2-in-12, adjusted as the referee deems appropriate. If the scout has a 16+ charisma, the base chance for being discerned is reduced to 1-in-12.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"scout","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Q7eHkvfQRl80TQBF"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252890133,"modifiedTime":1681579325696,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"WbfBFlBoxTbJEw2N","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
